[[File:Barrage Veianen vun ënne gesinn.jpg|thumb|[[Vianden Pumped Storage Plant]] in [[Diekirch District]]]]

'''[[Renewable energy]] in [[Luxembourg]]''' comes from [[hydro power]], [[wind]], [[biomass]] and [[solar power]].<ref name="erec">{{cite web|url=http://www.erec.org/fileadmin/erec_docs/Projcet_Documents/RES2020/LUXEMBOURG_RES_Policy_Review_09_Final.pdf|date=1 April 2009|author=ltesniere|title=RENEWABLE ENERGY POLICY REVIEW LUXEMBURG|accessdate=2014-08-23|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311084540/http://www.erec.org/fileadmin/erec_docs/Projcet_Documents/RES2020/LUXEMBOURG_RES_Policy_Review_09_Final.pdf|archivedate=11 March 2012|df=}}</ref>

==Policy==
Policy that supports renewable energy development in Luxembourg is the 1993 Framework Law (amended in 2005), in which there are special tariffs given to different type of renewable energy used and subsidies available for private companies that invest in renewable energy technology.

==Generation==
In 2005, renewable energy contributed to the 24.8% electricity generation in the country, which comprises pump storage (19.0%), hydro (2.3%), biomass (1.8%), wind (1.3%) and solar (0.4%).<ref name="energy">{{cite web|url=http://www.energy.eu/renewables/factsheets/2008_res_sheet_luxembourg_en.pdf|date=23 January 2008|title=Luxembourg Renewable Energy Fact Sheet|accessdate=2014-08-23}}</ref>

