The '''Rote Jahne Solar Park''' in [[Saxony]], [[Germany]], has a total output capacity of 6 megawatts peak (MWp). Built at a former military airfield, it has 90,000 [[First Solar]] [[Solar_cell#Thin_films|thin-film]] modules covering approximately 6.7 [[hectare]]s, and produces approximately 5.7 million kilowatt-hours (kW·h) of solar electricity every year.  The project cost around Euro 21 million or US $28 million.<ref name="thin-film">[http://www.renewableenergyaccess.com/rea/news/story?id=48027 Construction Complete on 6 MW Thin-Film PV Installation in Germany] ''Renewable Energy Access'', 5 April 2007.</ref>

